#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.137"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.137:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.137:0.2"
msgid "14. Yodhājīvavagga "
msgstr "14. A Warrior "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.137:0.3"
msgid "137. Kesakambalasutta "
msgstr "137. A Hair Blanket "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.137:1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yāni kānici tantāvutānaṃ vatthānaṃ, kesakambalo tesaṃ paṭikiṭṭho akkhāyati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a hair blanket is said to be the worst kind of woven cloth. "

msgctxt "an3.137:1.2"
msgid "Kesakambalo, bhikkhave, sīte sīto, uṇhe uṇho, dubbaṇṇo, duggandho, dukkhasamphasso. "
msgstr "It’s cold in the cold, hot in the heat, ugly, smelly, and unpleasant to touch. "

# NOTE: Note that BB has “various” here for puth, whereas he normally has “ordinary”. I think “various” is preferred always.
#. VAR: puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇavādānaṃ → puthusamaṇappavādānaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.137:1.3"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yāni kānici puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇavādānaṃ makkhalivādo tesaṃ paṭikiṭṭho akkhāyati. "
msgstr "In the same way, the teaching of Makkhali is said to be the worst of all the doctrines of the various ascetics and brahmins. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.287, sc2
msgctxt "an3.137:2.1"
msgid "Makkhali, bhikkhave, moghapuriso evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhi: "
msgstr "Makkhali, that silly man, has this doctrine and view: "

msgctxt "an3.137:2.2"
msgid "‘natthi kammaṃ, natthi kiriyaṃ, natthi vīriyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘There is no power in deeds, action, or energy.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.137:2.3"
msgid "Yepi te, bhikkhave, ahesuṃ atītamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, tepi bhagavanto kammavādā ceva ahesuṃ kiriyavādā ca vīriyavādā ca. "
msgstr "Now, all the perfected ones, the fully awakened Buddhas who lived in the past taught the efficacy of deeds, action, and energy. "

msgctxt "an3.137:2.4"
msgid "Tepi, bhikkhave, makkhali moghapuriso paṭibāhati: "
msgstr "But Makkhali opposes them by saying: "

msgctxt "an3.137:2.5"
msgid "‘natthi kammaṃ, natthi kiriyaṃ, natthi vīriyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘There is no power in deeds, action, or energy.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.137:2.6"
msgid "Yepi te, bhikkhave, bhavissanti anāgatamaddhānaṃ arahanto sammāsambuddhā, tepi bhagavanto kammavādā ceva bhavissanti kiriyavādā ca vīriyavādā ca. "
msgstr "All the perfected ones, the fully awakened Buddhas who will live in the future will teach the efficacy of deeds, action, and energy. "

msgctxt "an3.137:2.7"
msgid "Tepi, bhikkhave, makkhali moghapuriso paṭibāhati: "
msgstr "But Makkhali opposes them by saying: "

msgctxt "an3.137:2.8"
msgid "‘natthi kammaṃ, natthi kiriyaṃ, natthi vīriyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘There is no power in deeds, action, or energy.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.137:2.9"
msgid "Ahampi, bhikkhave, etarahi arahaṃ sammāsambuddho kammavādo ceva kiriyavādo ca vīriyavādo ca. "
msgstr "I too, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha in the present, teach the efficacy of deeds, action, and energy. "

msgctxt "an3.137:2.10"
msgid "Mampi, bhikkhave, makkhali moghapuriso paṭibāhati: "
msgstr "But Makkhali opposes me by saying: "

msgctxt "an3.137:2.11"
msgid "‘natthi kammaṃ, natthi kiriyaṃ, natthi vīriyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘There is no power in deeds, action, or energy.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
#. VAR: khippaṃ → khipaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: uḍḍeyya → oḍḍeyya (bj)
#. VAR: bahūnaṃ → bahunnaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.137:3.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, nadīmukhe khippaṃ uḍḍeyya bahūnaṃ macchānaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya anayāya byasanāya; "
msgstr "It’s like a trap set at the mouth of a river, which would bring harm, suffering, calamity, and disaster for many fish. "

msgctxt "an3.137:3.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, makkhali moghapuriso manussakhippaṃ maññe loke uppanno bahūnaṃ sattānaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya anayāya byasanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "In the same way that silly man Makkhali is a trap for humans, it seems to me. He has come into the world for the harm, suffering, calamity, and disaster of many beings.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.137:3.3"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

